  <!-- This reflects XML into a database.
       GameDB doesn't allow duplicate elements. The formatting is
       strange for XML, but good for the database.
   -->
  <tree>
    <research>
      <!-- Arrival needs to be the lowest points. It starts the plot. -->
      <Arrival points="10">
        We have long watched the aliens. Listened to the occasional strange
        digital chatter. A long frozen alien corpse sits in the deepest
        levels of our facility. Things are changing. The chatter is common now
        and we are picking up distant images on long range detectors.
      </Arrival>
      
      <!-- Alien genetics / reason to be here plotline -->
      <Green points="20">
        The same kind of creature is in the vaults from 70 years ago. Physically weak,
        mentally well developed, with reaction time within human ranges. Eyesight is 
        more adapted to darkness than ours, although the sight mechanisms are the same.
        The greens are much better adapted to night fighting than humans.
        <required0 item="Green" />
      </Green>
      <Hornet points="40">
        The Hornet is a fast, mobile alien assault troop. The Hornet is genetically a blend
        of the alien DNA we see in the Green with another race. The Greens or their masters
        must be assimilating the genetics of other creatures.
        <required0 research="Green" />
        <required1 item="Hornet" />
      </Hornet>
      <Viper points="40">
        The Viper is a heavy alien assault troop with significant natural armor. Like the Hornet,
        the Viper is a genetic blend. The genetic sources seem to indicate that the Hornet and Viper
        are not from the Green's homeworld.
        <required0 research="Green" />
        <required2 item="Viper" />
      </Viper>
      <Jackal points="60">
        The Jackal is a cybort based on robotics and an alien creature. The creature - whatever it
        is and wherever it from - is genetically distict yet again from the other aliens.
        <required0 research="Green" />
        <required2 item="Jackal" />
      </Jackal>
      <Prime points="80">
        The Prime and Green and lesser and greater creatures of the same race perhaps.
        Very similar, yet the Prime is clearly the more intelligent with better
        physical attributes as well. Clearly the ruling class. We must conclude that
        the aliens are conquering and integrating the galaxy.
        <required0 item="Prime" />
        <required1 research="Green" />
        <required2 research="Hornet" />
        <required3 research="Viper" />
      </Prime>

      <!-- UFOs and Alien Base Plotline -->
      <UFOs points="40" >
        We have detected 3 classes of UFOs, which we refer to as the Scout, Frigate,
        and Battleship. Something the size of the Battleship will never be able to
        land on the Earth's surface; we're not sure how to attack it assuming it 
        can hover like the other alien ships.
        <required0 research="Arrival" />
      </UFOs>
      <AlienCores points="40">
        We have retrieved an alien computer core. It is strange and adaptive, and
        much of its purpose is inscruitable. But by connecting it to alien components
        and our own sensors, we are beginning to get new information on the alien agenda.
        <required0 item="Cor:S" />
      </AlienCores>
      <Scout points="40">
        The Scout is a small ship undoubtlable responsible for many alient abductions
        and sightings in the past. Why they leave crop circles as a part of their
        abduction/scanning missions is a mystery. They hover for a short amount of
        time and can be intercepted on land. 
        <required0 research="AlienCores" />
      </Scout>
      <AlienTech points="40">
        Alien weapons show tech classes we've designated T1, T2, and T3.
        Whether higher tech weapons reflect manufacturing cost or alien
        social status is unclear.
        <required0 research="AlienCores" />
      </AlienTech>
      <Cell points="60">
        We have research techniques to field stabilize the alien cells used to power
        alien weapons. We can also charge them at the base. You may now collect cells in the field.
        <required0 item="Cor:S" />
        <required1 research="Hornet" />
      </Cell>
      <Anti points="80">
        We have research techniques to field stabilize the alien anti-matter cells used in high
        power alien weapons. We can also charge them at the base. You may now collect cells in the field.
        <required0 item="Cor:F" />
        <required1 research="Viper" />
        <required2 research="Cell" />
      </Anti>
      <Frigate points="40">
        The Frigate is a medium ship suited for both crop cirlcle missions and city
        attack. It can carry about 12 aliens with full armament. The frigate computer 
        core is larger than the Scout core, and it's navigation system is configured
        differently. We need to research a Battleship core to compare the systems.
        <required0 research="AlienTech" />
        <required1 research="Scout" />
        <required2 item="Cor:F" />
      </Frigate>
      <BattleshipAttack points="80">
        The Battleships never come out of hover, and we have struggled with how to
        attack them. The Frigate core contains the ability to authenticate with the
        Battleships. We believe this can be used to dock our lander with a Battleship.
        Obviously a very risky mission.
        <required0 research="AlienTech" />
        <required1 research="Scout" />
        <required2 item="Cor:F" />
      </BattleshipAttack>
      <Battleship points="120">
        The Battleship is well named. A fully capable alien vessel with massive firepower,
        including a main downward facing gun for city control or base destruction. Even more
        intriguing however is that the navigation system is based on a homing technology.
        There must be a beacon, here on Earth, calling the Battleships!
        <required0 item="Cor:B" />
      </Battleship>
      <Beacon points="200">
        The beacon has been located. Without the ability to navigate over deep space, the
        alien threat will be highly compromised. We feel confident that the beacon is
        very heavily guarded.
        <required0 research="Battleship" />
      </Beacon>

      <!-- Items -->
      <ASLT-2 points="40">
        Description Needed
        <required1 item="RAY-2" />  <!-- was PLS, but PLS is hard to get w/o destroyer. And destroyer hard to get without ALST-2 -->
      </ASLT-2>      
      <ASLT-3 points="60">
        Description Needed
        <required0 research="Hornet" />
        <required1 research="ASLT-2" />
        <required2 item="PLS-3" />
      </ASLT-3>

